CSCI345_HW1
Reid Foster, Ethan Guthrie

Run the script using the following syntax:
    python Foster_Guthrie_HW1_passwd_cracking.py <input_file>
NOTE:   Functionality of this script is only guarunteed for systems running
        Linux/macOS. Still, Windows systems should be able to run this
        script if they specify a dictionary.

input_file is assumed to be a text file containing password hashes in the
following format:
    Username:SHA-256_Password[:optional_parameters]


word_file is assumed to be a text file containing a list of dictionary words
separated one per line which is assumed to be /usr/share/dict/words unless
otherwise specified.